          "merged_at": "2025-10-06T05:17:23Z"
        },
        "body": " Minimum Window Substring \r\n\r\nThis Python solution efficiently finds the smallest substring in a given string s that contains all the characters of another string t, including duplicates.\r\nIt uses a sliding window + hashmap approach to achieve optimal performance.\r\n\r\n- Approach\r\n\r\nUse a sliding window to dynamically expand and shrink the range of characters in s.\r\n\r\nMaintain a frequency counter (Counter) for the characters in t.\r\n\r\nExpand the right pointer until all characters are matched.\r\n\r\nThen, move the left pointer to minimize the window size while keeping all required characters.\r\n\r\nKeep track of the smallest valid window throughout.\r\n\r\n- Complexity\r\n\r\nTime Complexity: O(n) — each character is visited at most twice.\r\n\r\nSpace Complexity: O(k) — where k is the number of unique characters in t.",
        "reactions": {
